Next Generation of javascript summary
Next-generation JavaScript could be thought of as the latest version of ECMAScript, the standardized specification for JavaScript.

Each version endeavors to improve upon and add new functionality to this increasingly popular programming language. JavaScript has taken over the world of software development.

Next-generation JavaScript uses arrow functions, let, const, and other updated syntax. Modern React apps typically use these updated features of the JavaScript language.

According to Codeburst.io, JavaScript is the top programming language for developers.JavaScript: ES6 and ES7
